<p><strong>Why was it wrong? Why does your fix work?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Bug C</strong> — Horizontal and vertical checks should be separate. Right now they happen in one move, and the player jitters and gets stuck in corners.</p>
<pre><code class="language-python">player.x += vx
player.y += vy
for plat in platforms:
    if player.colliderect(plat):
        player.right = plat.left
        player.bottom = plat.top
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Hint:</strong> move on X and resolve X first, <em>then</em> move on Y and resolve Y.</p>
<p><strong>Write the fixed code:</strong></p>
